  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Lucia Weston tells of an important letter from Amos A. Phelps to Mrs. Maria W. Chapman. When the letter arrived, &quot;they exclaimed with one voice, &apos;here&apos;s richness.&apos;&quot; Lucia gives some news of Weymouth. She tells about a trip to Lowell in the train. On page 2 of the manuscript, is a transcription of the letter sent by Amos A. Phelps to Mrs. Maria W. Chapman. Lucia mentions that Benjamin Lundy died.</subfield>
